title: Which Israel Will Emerge After the Hamas Attack?
description: The good Israel will destroy Hamas' military—and it must also prevail over Netanyahu's government.

title: Workers at Mack Trucks Go on Strike, Joining Thousands of UAW Picketers
description: The UAW said 4,000 unionized workers walked out at 7 a.m., adding to labor turmoil in the industry that has ensnared all three big Detroit automakers.

title: ‘I Was Saved by a Miracle.’ A Survivor Recounts the Horror of the Hamas Attack on Israel’s Supernova Festival
description: At least 260 bodies have been found dead from the music festival following Hamas' suprise attack on Saturday.

title: Heavy Flooding in Myanmar Displaces More Than 14,000 People
description: Bago township in Southern Myanmar recorded 7.87 inches of rainfall, its highest level in 59 years.

title: Robert F. Kennedy Jr. to Run for President as an Independent, Drop Democratic Primary Bid
description: Robert F. Kennedy Jr., part of one of the most famous Democratic families in politics, said he will run for president as an independent.

title: Flag Football Could Become an Olympic Sport in 2028
description: The International Olympic Committee will vote on the proposal at meetings in Mumbai, along with proposals for baseball, squash, and cricket, among others.

title: Israel’s President: Our Darkest Hour Casts a Shadow on the Entire World
description: As many around the world offer support to Israel in the wake of Hamas' brutal attacks, writes the President of Israel, 'platitudes and sympathies must translate into tangible support.'

title: U.S. Raises Death Toll to 9 of Americans Killed in Hamas Attacks on Israel
description: The State Department said at least nine American citizens have been killed in the weekend Hamas attacks on Israel, raising the toll from four.

title: Michael Lewis Likens Critics of His New Book on Sam Bankman-Fried to a ‘Mob’
description: The author spoke to TIME about 'Going Infinite' and why he thinks most people misunderstand Sam Bankman-Fried.

title: The Frasier Revival Serves Up Wilted Salads and Expired Eggs
description: Kelsey Grammer leads an all-new cast in this Paramount+ sequel series that's precisely as dire as it sounds.

title: Nobel Economics Prize Goes to Claudia Goldin for Research on Workplace Gender Gap
description: Her research has advanced the understanding of the gender gap in the labor market.

title: Chuck Schumer Blasts Xi Jinping Over China’s Israel-Hamas Stance as Senators Visit Beijing
description: The other issues on the agenda concern Chinese companies’ role in the fentanyl crisis in the U.S. and human rights.

title: Some Republicans Want Less Aid for Ukraine and More for Taiwan—But Taiwan Doesn’t
description: Taiwan and its supporters say China is watching closely to see if the U.S. has the political stamina to support an ally in a prolonged, costly war.

title: China Calls for Ceasefire, ‘Two-State Solution’ Amid Conflict Between Hamas, Israel
description: Beijing repeated its support for a “two-state solution,” calling it the fundamental way out of the conflict.

title: Biden’s Twin Crises: Possible U.S. Hostages, Risks of Wider War
description: Biden was briefed on the Hamas attack, called allies, and deployed air and naval forces to the eastern Mediterranean Sea near Israel.
